narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: It's an extension of Cell Biology. I've learned more about some topics. It's useful to know the advances, and some interesting questions and communicate with other students and professors.
Critical thoughts of the paper, different interesting topic in various field of Molecular cell biology
Interpret results, analyse purpose behind experiments, ask further questions to a paper. Understand literature in a much deeper level.
I learned how to critically analyze a paper.

Throughout this course, I believe I gained valuable experience in reading papers critically and being able to understand articles from various fields. I feel that in the future I will be better equipped to read scientific articles and also to write in scientific jargon.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It's an extension of Cell Biology. I've learned more about some topics. It's useful to know the advances, and some interesting questions and communicate with other students and professors.
Topics covered almost all fields of cell biology

I think it was a very important course, and I have learnt a lot from it. I think that for a couple of weeks it was not well synchronized with 602 because we had to read the paper before the lecture, but in general it helped me deepen the knowledge acquired in 602 and understand things much better.
I liked this course because it was highly discussion based. No weaknesses of which to speak.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: recommend.It's useful to know the advances, and some interesting questions and communicate with other students and professors.
Yes, it is great for everyone interested in cell biology in general. It really helps understanding 602 lectures much better.
Yes. All graduate students need to learn how to analyze scientific literature and understand their relevance.
Yes I would recommend this course to other students because I found it to be an interesting course that was beneficial to my learning.
